Package alix.lucene.search

Class FieldRail

  • java.lang.Object
    • alix.lucene.search.FieldRail
  • public class FieldRail
extends Object
    Persistent storage of full sequence of all document search for a field. Used for co-occurrences stats. Data structure of the file

    int:maxDoc, maxDoc*[int:docLength], maxDoc*[docLength*[int:formId], int:-1]

    Author:
    fred

      • freqs

        public long[] freqs​(org.apache.lucene.util.BitSet filter)
             throws IOException
        From a set of documents provided as a BitSet, return a freqlist as an int vector, where index is the formId for the field, the value is count of occurrences of the term. Counts are extracted from stored rails.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • coocs

        public long coocs​(FormEnum dic)
           throws IOException
        Build a cooccurrence freqList in formId order, attached to a FormEnum object. This oculd be sorted after in different manner accordin to Specif. Returns the count of occurences found.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • score

        public void score​(FormEnum dic)
        Scores a FormEnum with freqs extracted by coocs(FormEnum). For the Specif algorithm, the search and co-occurrences contexts are considered as a part in the corpus. For tf-idf like scoring, this part is considered like a single document.

      • rail

        public void rail​(org.apache.lucene.index.Terms termVector,
                 IntList buf)
          throws IOException
        Flatten search of a document in a position order, according to the dictionary of search. Write it in a binary buffer, ready to to be stored in a BinaryField. BinaryDocValuesField The buffer could be modified if resizing was needed.
        Parameters:
        termVector - A term vector of a document with positions.
        buf - A reusable binary buffer to index.

        IOException
